reger","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Gregory</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Gregers","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Gregory</b> ."]},{"name":"Gregory","meanings":["Via Latin <i>Gregorius</i> from the post-classical Greek name <i>Gregōrios</i> ‘watchful’ (a derivative of <i>gregōrein</i> ‘to watch, be vigilant’). The name was a very popular one among the early Christians, who were mindful of the injunction ‘be sober, be vigilant’ (1 Peter 5:8). It was borne by a number of early saints. The most important, in honour of whom the name was often bestowed from medieval times onwards, were Gregory of Nazianzen (  <i>c.</i>329–90 ), Gregory of Nyssa (  d. <i>c.</i>395 ), Gregory of Tours (  538–94 ), and  Pope Gregory the Great  (  <i>c.</i>540–604 ). A famous bearer of the name in modern times is the film star  Gregory Peck  (  1916–2003 ). The name has traditionally been popular in Scotland, where it is often found in the form  <b>Gregor</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Greger Djaekne was born about 1390. She married Greger Djekn Örnflycht about 1424, in Sweden. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters."},"et":{"about 1390–":"umbes 1390–Surnud","1416–1445":"1416–1445","1402–1472":"1402–1472","1404–Female":"1404–Surnud","1415–1481":"1415–1481","1390–Female":"1390–Surnud","abt. 1415":"umbes 1415","about 1390":"umbes 1390","Abt 1424":"umbes 1424","1472":"1472","1481":"1481","1390":"1390","1415":"1415","1404":"1404","abt 1402":"umbes 1402","1402":"1402","1445":"1445","abt 1404":"umbes 1404","1416":"1416","Sweden":"Rootsi","Granhammar, Uppsala, Sweden":"Granhammar, Västra Ryd, Uppsala, Rootsi","of Granhammar, Upland, Sweden":"Granhammar, Västra Ryd, Uppsala, Rootsi"},"fi":{"about 1390–":"noin 1390–Kuollut","1416–1445":"1416–1445","1402–1472":"1402–1472","1404–Female":"1404–Kuollut","1415–1481":"1415–1481","1390–Female":"1390–Kuollut","abt. 1415":"noin 1415","